    "ML and AI researchers have raised many questions about the source and the solution to the fairness issues in AI (FAI) and discussed various types of biases [10].ML models can exhibit various unfairness issues, encompassing biases and discriminatory outcomes.",
    "Discussions often revolve around biases in training datasets, discriminatory behavior exhibited by predictive models, and the challenge of interpreting and explaining the outcomes produced by these models.",
    "Biases in the training dataset usually refer to the data representing disparities and discrimination against certain groups based on attributes such as race, gender, or socioeconomic status, which Ml models may inadvertently amplify.",
    "The press and literature gradually started to discuss these types of ML model bias in the early twentyfirst century [11,12].",
    "Also, ML models can exhibit bias towards specific groups despite unbiased training data."
